      [
        "p",
        {},
        "In Modern Greek, the accent mark (",
        [
          "span",
          {
            "className": "greek-text"
          },
          "ο τόνος"
        ],
        ") is a crucial orthographic feature that indicates which syllable\n            of a word is stressed. Unlike English, where stress patterns can be\n            ambiguous, Greek uses a visible mark to ensure correct\n            pronunciation."
      ],
      [
        "h2",
        {},
        "The Fundamental Rules"
      ],
      [
        "ul",
        {},
        [
          "li",
          {},
          [
            "strong",
            {},
            "Target:"
          ],
          " ",
          "The accent goes",
          " ",
          [
            "strong",
            {},
            "only"
          ],
          " ",
          "on\n                top of vowels."
        ],
        [
          "li",
          {},
          [
            "strong",
            {},
            "Position:"
          ],
          " ",
          "Only the last three syllables of a word\n                can carry an accent."
        ],
        [
          "li",
          {},
          [
            "strong",
            {},
            "Monosyllables:"
          ],
          " ",
          "Words with only one syllable generally\n                do not take an accent (with a few grammatical exceptions)."
        ]
      ],
